Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity

- Total Liabilities (end amount) = Total Current Liabilities = $7,605,149.91
- Total Owner's Equity (end amount) = $16,112,375.10

Now I'll calculate the ratio:
Debt to Equity Ratio = $7,605,149.91 / $16,112,375.10 = 0.47201...

Rounding to 2 decimal places: 0.47
